<h1>IT 2008 Database Systems — Practical Cheatsheet</h1>
<p>Quick reference of commands and queries for the practical exam: <strong>PostgreSQL · MongoDB · Redis</strong>. Examples use the <em>gamehub</em> / university sample data.</p>

<hr>
<h2>1 · PostgreSQL (SQL)</h2>

<h3>Basic SELECT / filter / sort</h3>
<pre>SELECT * FROM games;
SELECT title, price FROM games;                 -- pick columns
SELECT DISTINCT genre FROM games;               -- unique values
SELECT * FROM games WHERE price &gt; 20;            -- &lt; &gt; &gt;= &lt;= = &lt;&gt;
SELECT * FROM games WHERE genre = 'Shooter' AND multiplayer = TRUE;
SELECT * FROM games WHERE genre IN ('Shooter','Racing');
SELECT * FROM games WHERE price BETWEEN 10 AND 30;
SELECT * FROM players WHERE country IS NOT NULL;
SELECT * FROM games ORDER BY price DESC;         -- ASC default
SELECT * FROM games ORDER BY price DESC LIMIT 5; -- top 5</pre>

<h3>LIKE / pattern / CASE / COALESCE</h3>
<pre>WHERE username LIKE 'a%'    -- starts with a   (% = many chars, _ = one char)
WHERE email LIKE '%gmail%'  -- contains
ILIKE                        -- case-insensitive
COALESCE(manager_id, 0)      -- first non-NULL
CASE WHEN price = 0 THEN 'Free' WHEN price &lt; 20 THEN 'Cheap' ELSE 'Premium' END</pre>

<h3>Aggregates + GROUP BY / HAVING</h3>
<pre>SELECT COUNT(*), AVG(price), SUM(price), MIN(price), MAX(price) FROM games;
SELECT genre, COUNT(*) FROM games GROUP BY genre;
SELECT genre, AVG(price) FROM games GROUP BY genre HAVING AVG(price) &gt; 20;
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT genre) FROM games;</pre>

<h3>Joins</h3>
<pre>-- INNER: only matches
SELECT g.title, s.name FROM games g JOIN studios s ON g.studio_id = s.studio_id;
-- LEFT: keep all left rows (NULL where no match)  + COALESCE for 0
SELECT g.title, COALESCE(SUM(p.amount_paid),0) AS revenue
FROM games g LEFT JOIN purchases p ON p.game_id = g.game_id
GROUP BY g.title;
-- RIGHT JOIN, FULL OUTER JOIN, CROSS JOIN (cartesian) also exist
-- self join
SELECT a.title, b.title FROM games a JOIN games b ON a.price = b.price AND a.game_id &lt; b.game_id;</pre>

<h3>Subqueries / set operations</h3>
<pre>SELECT * FROM games WHERE price &gt; (SELECT AVG(price) FROM games);
SELECT * FROM players WHERE player_id IN (SELECT player_id FROM purchases);
-- set ops (same columns/types):
SELECT col FROM a UNION SELECT col FROM b;       -- distinct
SELECT col FROM a UNION ALL SELECT col FROM b;   -- keep dups
... INTERSECT ...   ... EXCEPT ...</pre>

<h3>Window functions</h3>
<pre>RANK()       OVER (ORDER BY score DESC)
ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY genre ORDER BY price DESC)
DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY salary DESC)
SUM(amount) OVER (ORDER BY day)                       -- running total
AVG(score)  OVER (ORDER BY day ROWS BETWEEN 2 PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW)
NTILE(4)    OVER (ORDER BY price)                      -- quartiles
LAG(price)  OVER (ORDER BY price)
-- % of partition total:
price * 100.0 / SUM(price) OVER (PARTITION BY genre)</pre>

<h3>CTE (WITH) / recursion</h3>
<pre>WITH top AS (SELECT player_id, SUM(amount_paid) tot FROM purchases GROUP BY player_id)
SELECT * FROM top WHERE tot &gt; (SELECT AVG(tot) FROM top);

WITH RECURSIVE chain AS (
  SELECT id, manager_id, 1 AS lvl FROM emp WHERE manager_id IS NULL
  UNION ALL
  SELECT e.id, e.manager_id, c.lvl+1 FROM emp e JOIN chain c ON e.manager_id = c.id)
SELECT * FROM chain;</pre>

<h3>ROLLUP / CUBE (subtotals &amp; cross-tabs)</h3>
<pre>SELECT genre, player_country, SUM(amount_paid)
FROM game_sales_report
GROUP BY ROLLUP (genre, player_country);          -- subtotal per genre + grand total

SELECT studio_country, premium, SUM(amount_paid)
FROM game_sales_report
GROUP BY CUBE (studio_country, premium);           -- every combination + all subtotals</pre>

<h3>Full-text search</h3>
<pre>-- match both words:
WHERE to_tsvector('english', body) @@ to_tsquery('english','space &amp; shooter')
-- OR:  'space | shooter'    NOT: '!space'
ts_rank(to_tsvector('english', body), to_tsquery('english','space &amp; shooter'))  -- relevance
plainto_tsquery('english','space shooter')     -- plain words (AND)
phraseto_tsquery('english','space shooter')    -- exact adjacent phrase
websearch_to_tsquery('english','survival crafting')  -- web-style query
ts_headline('english', body, to_tsquery('english','space &amp; shooter'))  -- highlighted snippet
-- index it:  CREATE INDEX idx ON reviews USING gin(to_tsvector('english', body));</pre>

<h3>Fuzzy matching / INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE / DDL</h3>
<pre>levenshtein('bat','fads')          -- edit distance
title % 'Avatre'                    -- trigram similarity (pg_trgm)
metaphone('Broos',6)               -- phonetic

INSERT INTO studios (name, country) VALUES ('New','UK');
UPDATE games SET price = price * 0.9 WHERE genre = 'RPG';
DELETE FROM games WHERE price = 0;

CREATE VIEW v AS SELECT ...;                 -- stored query
CREATE INDEX i ON games USING btree (price); -- hash for equality, gin/gist for FTS
BEGIN; ... COMMIT;   |   ROLLBACK;           -- transaction</pre>

<hr>
<h2>2 · MongoDB</h2>

<h3>find / projection / sort</h3>
<pre>db.games.find()                                  // all
db.games.find({ genre: 'Shooter' })
db.games.find({ price: { $gt: 20 } })            // $lt $lte $gt $gte $ne
db.games.find({ genre: { $in: ['Shooter','Racing'] } })   // $nin
db.games.find({ price: { $gte: 10, $lte: 30 } })
db.games.find({ multiplayer: true })
db.games.find({}, { title: 1, _id: 0 })          // projection: 1 include, 0 exclude
db.games.find().sort({ price: -1 }).limit(5)      // -1 desc, 1 asc
db.games.find().sort({ price: -1 }).skip(5).limit(5)   // paging
db.games.findOne({ title: 'Dune' })
db.games.countDocuments({ genre: 'RPG' })
db.games.distinct('genre')</pre>

<h3>Operators (criteria)</h3>
<pre>{ tags: 'victory' }                     // array contains value
{ tags: { $all: ['solo','ranked'] } }   // contains all
{ tags: { $size: 3 } }                  // array length
{ field: { $exists: true } }
{ 'mayor.party': 'D' }                  // dot notation (nested)
{ $or: [ {a:1}, {b:2} ] }               // $and $nor
{ title: /^The/ }                       // regex   (or { $regex:'war', $options:'i' })
{ arr: { $elemMatch: { x:1, y:true } } }// conditions within ONE element</pre>

<h3>insert / update / delete</h3>
<pre>db.games.insertOne({ title:'X', price:9 })
db.games.updateOne({ title:'Dune' }, { $set: { inStock: true } })   // WITHOUT $ = replaces doc!
db.games.updateMany({ price:{$lt:15} }, { $set:{ onSale:true } })
// update operators: $set $unset $inc $mul $push $addToSet $pull $pop $rename
db.games.deleteMany({ rating: { $lt: 2 } })</pre>

<h3>Aggregation pipeline (stages run in order)</h3>
<pre>db.sessions.aggregate([
  { $match:  { premium: true } },                         // filter (like WHERE)
  { $unwind: '$tags' },                                   // array -> one row per element
  { $group:  { _id: '$gameTitle', total: { $sum: '$score' },
               avg: { $avg:'$durationMin' }, players: { $addToSet:'$username' } } },
  { $match:  { total: { $gte: 1000 } } },                 // HAVING
  { $sort:   { total: -1 } },                             // -1 desc
  { $limit:  3 },
  { $project:{ _id:0, gameTitle:'$_id', total:1,
               distinctPlayers: { $size: '$players' } } } // reshape output
])
// accumulators: $sum $avg $min $max $push $addToSet $first $last
// other stages: $skip $count $addFields $bucket $bucketAuto $facet $lookup</pre>

<h3>Common patterns</h3>
<pre>// count per group, reshaped
db.sessions.aggregate([{ $group:{ _id:'$genre', n:{$sum:1} } },
  { $sort:{ n:-1 } }, { $project:{ _id:0, genre:'$_id', n:1 } }])

// distinct count via $addToSet + $size
{ $group:{ _id:'$gameTitle', u:{ $addToSet:'$username' } } },
{ $project:{ _id:0, gameTitle:'$_id', players:{ $size:'$u' } } }

// month from a date
{ $group:{ _id:{ $dateToString:{ format:'%Y-%m', date:'$playedOn' } }, n:{$sum:1} } }

// join two collections
{ $lookup:{ from:'games', localField:'gameTitle', foreignField:'title', as:'g' } },
{ $unwind:'$g' }, { $project:{ username:1, price:'$g.price' } }

// conditional value
{ $project:{ cat:{ $cond:[ { $gt:['$durationMin',90] }, 'long', 'short' ] } } }</pre>

<hr>
<h2>3 · Redis</h2>

<h3>Strings / counters</h3>
<pre>SET total_students 5            GET total_students
SETNX key val                  // set only if not exists
SETEX key 30 val               // set + 30s expiry
INCR total_students   DECR ...  INCRBY key 10   DECRBY key 5
APPEND key " more"   STRLEN key   GETRANGE key 0 3   GETSET key new
MSET a 1 b 2          MGET a b</pre>

<h3>Hashes (objects)  — H*</h3>
<pre>HSET student:1003 name "Maria" gpa 3.9
HGET student:1003 gpa          HGETALL student:1003
HMGET student:1003 name gpa    HKEYS k   HVALS k   HLEN k
HEXISTS student:1003 gpa       HDEL student:1003 status
HINCRBY student:1001 year 1</pre>

<h3>Lists (queue/stack)  — L*/R*</h3>
<pre>RPUSH q a b c                  // push right (tail)   LPUSH = push left (head)
LRANGE q 0 -1                  // all (−1 = last)
LLEN q   LINDEX q 0            LPOP q   RPOP q
LSET q 0 first   LTRIM q 0 2   // keep first 3
RPOPLPUSH src dst             // atomic move
BLPOP q 5                      // blocking pop (wait 5s)</pre>

<h3>Sets (unique, unordered)  — S*</h3>
<pre>SADD course:CS101:students 1001 1002    SREM set m
SMEMBERS set   SCARD set   SISMEMBER set 1004   // 1/0
SINTER a b     SUNION a b   SDIFF a b
SMOVE src dst member          SUNIONSTORE dest a b</pre>

<h3>Sorted sets (score-ordered)  — Z*</h3>
<pre>ZADD course:CS101:grades 88 1001 75 1002 91 1003
ZSCORE z member        ZINCRBY z 5 member        ZCARD z
ZRANGE z 0 -1 WITHSCORES        // low -&gt; high
ZREVRANGE z 0 -1 WITHSCORES     // high -&gt; low   (top N: 0 N-1)
ZRANGEBYSCORE z 90 +inf WITHSCORES     // by score  (( = exclusive)
ZCOUNT z 80 100        ZRANK z m   ZREVRANK z m
ZPOPMAX z   ZPOPMIN z   ZREMRANGEBYRANK z 0 0
ZUNIONSTORE dest 2 z1 z2 WEIGHTS 1 2</pre>

<h3>Expiry / keys / transactions / pub-sub</h3>
<pre>EXPIRE key 60   PEXPIRE key 5000   TTL key   PERSIST key
EXISTS key   DEL key   TYPE key   RENAME a b
SCAN 0 MATCH student:*        KEYS pattern (avoid in prod)
-- transaction (atomic block):
MULTI
  SADD student:1005:courses CS102
  SADD course:CS102:students 1005
EXEC                          // DISCARD cancels;  WATCH key = optimistic lock
-- messaging:  SUBSCRIBE channel    PUBLISH channel "msg"
-- persistence:  RDB snapshots (SAVE/BGSAVE) · AOF append-only log</pre>

<hr>
<p class="t">Remember:</p>
<p>• <strong>WHERE</strong> filters rows, <strong>HAVING</strong> filters groups · <strong>%</strong>=many, <strong>_</strong>=one · window funcs keep rows (<code>OVER</code>), aggregates collapse them.<br>
• Mongo: operators are <code>$op</code>; <code>$set</code> on updates or you replace the whole doc; aggregation ≈ WHERE+GROUP BY+ORDER BY; pick by stage order (<code>$match</code> early).<br>
• Redis: the command letter tells the type — <code>H</code>=hash, <code>L/R</code>=list, <code>S</code>=set, <code>Z</code>=sorted set; <code>MULTI/EXEC</code> = transaction; <code>EXPIRE/TTL</code> = caching.</p>

</body>
</html>
